  ],
  "returns": "Configuration or NULL if the operation fails",
  "remarks": "If the specified configuration has not been activated, then some data may be unavailable. For example, attempting to traverse assembly components for a configuration that has not been activated results in a NULL root component being returned from\nIConfiguration::GetRootComponent\n. However, the IConfiguration object returned is useful for obtaining data that is stored with the IConfiguration object, such as the\nIConfiguration::AlternateName\nvalue. The specified configuration does not have to be activated to obtain this type of stored information.",
